message.content:
We only need to sum up the amount on the “Initial20231231001” lines because these represent the capital contributed when the company was formed. In our table there are three such transactions:
• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 5,000,000.0  

Their total is 3,000,000 + 5,000,000 + 5,000,000 = 13,000,000.0.

Since no later transactions affect the paid‐in capital, both the initial and the end (final) values remain at 13,000,000.00.

Below is the answer in the required JSON format.

--------------------------------------------------

{"solution": {"Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "13000000.00", "Paid-in Capital End Value": "13000000.00"}}
